name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Venezuelans protest outside the United Nations office in Caracas.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: At one o'clock in the afternoon, presidential candidate and opposition leader Edmundo González, surrounded by the crowd, marched towards Francisco de Miranda Avenue to the rally site at the United Nations Office in Caracas.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Venezuelans throw ink on Chavez's portrait

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: At this moment, outside the United Nations Office in Caracas, people are surging

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Opposition leader Edmundo Gonzalez receives a warm cheer from the crowd

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Venezuelan Army Captains Javier and Juan Carlos publicly called on the military: "At this historic moment, it is time to make the right decision... It is clear that we have a new president."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On July 29, a 17-year-old boy broke into a dance school in Southport, England, with a knife, killing three children and injuring 10 others.
Earlier on the 30th, government officials including the prime minister came to mourn, but were criticized by the public. At the same time, a large-scale anti-immigration protest broke out at the scene

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Opposition leader Maria Collina announced at the rally that Edmundo Gonzalez would become the new president of Venezuela. Maduro's troops then began to crack down and fired tear gas to disperse the crowd. Maria Collina accompanied the injured to the hospital.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Just now, former Venezuelan President Maduro made a live televised speech accusing Elon Musk of being behind the Venezuelan protests and accusing Musk of allying with the Biden administration and Colombian drug traffickers to overthrow him.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Maduro and Musk still have a grudge

Earlier, Maduro accused Musk of trying to use his rockets and "army" to invade Venezuela. He also wanted to fight Musk.

In response, Musk said on the 29th that "donkeys know more than Maduro" and then apologized to the donkey.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Venezuelans fought off police who tried to suppress them on Route Carrera 3 in Guanare, Portuguesa state.
